site_name: Town Hall Annexe And Brian Didsbury Centre, 330-354
description: Section 73 application to vary Condition 2 (Approved plans and documents) to reflect a change in the tenure of 71 homes from Private Rented Sector units to London Affordable Rent. The change of tenure will be secured by a s.106 Obligation attached to planning permission 16/02824/FUL dated 19th September 2018 which was granted permission for: Demolition of non-original additions to the rear of the Town Hall Annex and demolition of The Didsbury Centre; refurbishment of the Town Hall Annex and the erection of a two storey roof extension; change of use of the Town Hall Annexe from B1(a) Offices to C3 residential use and A3 restaurant/cafe at ground floor and erection of two new residential buildings, to provide 185 residential units; landscaping, car and cycle parking and associated works. This application falls within East Ham Civic Conservation Area This application affects the setting of a Conservation Area This application affects the setting of the following Listed Buildings: - Technical College Library ,Barking Road, Grade II - Town Hall, 324 Barking Road, Grade II star -
